criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  regular menstruation with intervals of 21-35 days;

          -  cycle length variations <4 days;

          -  both ovaries still present

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  history of liver failure;

          -  diagnosed malignancy;

          -  cigarette smoking;

          -  chronic renal failure;

          -  known infertility;

          -  presence of gynecological abnormalities such as abnormal uterine bleeding or
             menorrhagia;

          -  history of ovarian surgery;

          -  history of hormone preparation (including corticosteroids) use or use of herbal
             products within 3 months;

          -  diagnosis of polycystic ovary syndrome.
